."],"variants":[{"name":"Mansfield","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place so named in Nottinghamshire. The placename means ‘open land by the river Maun’, from the river name Maun (which may take its name from a hill named with Old English <i>mamme</i> ‘teat’) + Old English <i>feld</i> ‘open country’.","Irish (Waterford): when not an importation of 1, this is an altered form of the Norman name <b>de Manville</b> (see   Mandeville   3).","Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic) <b>Mansfeld</b>, a habitational name from a place so called in Saxony."]},{"name":"Manderville","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Mandeville  ."]},{"name":"Manwell","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Mandeville  ."]},{"name":"Manville","meanings":["English (Sussex and Lancashire): variant of   Mandeville  .","Altered form of   Mainville   1, a surname of Swiss French origin (see   Miville  ).","French: variant of <b>Menville</b>, a habitational name from Menville in Haute-Garonne, and also of   Mainville   2."]},{"name":"Mundell","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Mandeville  .","Americanized form of German <b>Mündel</b> (or some other similar, like-sounding surname): nickname for someone with a prominent mouth, from Middle High German <i>munt</i>, <i>mündelīn</i> ‘(little) mouth’."]},{"name":"Monville","meanings":["Altered form of French   Mandeville  .","Walloon: habitational name from Monville in Namur province in Wallonia (Belgium), of the same etymology as in 3 below.","In some cases possibly also French: habitational name from Montville in Seine-Maritime or Monville in Calvados, both named with Old French <i>mont</i> ‘mountain, hill’ + <i>ville</i> ‘settlement’."]},{"name":"Mandal","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Chandi, Sanjay, Sankar, Somnath, Aditi, Aditya, Ajit, Amala, Amitabha, Anil, Anirudh, Aparna.","Indian (northern states): from Sanskrit <i>maṇḍala</i>, a word that has several meanings, including ‘sphere’ and ‘halo’.","English (Cumbria; of Norman origin): variant of   Mandeville  ."]},{"name":"Montville","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Vernice.","Altered form of French   Mandeville  .","French: variant of   Monville  . This surname is very rare in France, found mainly in Creuse."]},{"name":"Manfull","meanings":["English (Midlands): probably a variant of   Mandeville  . Compare   Manville  ."]}]},{"name":"Karmine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Masculine form of   Carmela  , influenced by Latin <i>carminis</i>, genitive of <i>carmen</i> ‘song’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Karmine Manneville was born in 1198, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Henry de Glanville."},"et":{"1198–":"1198–Surnud","1184–1230":"1184–1230","1217–1272":"1217–1272","1198–Female":"1198–Surnud","1217":"1217","1198":"1198","1230":"1230","1272":"1272","1184":"1184","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1198–":"1198–Kuollut","1184–1230":"1184–1230","1217–1272":"1217–1272","1198–Female":"1198–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1198":"1198","1230":"1230","1272":"1272","1184":"1184","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1198–":"1198–Décédée","1184–1230":"1184–1230","1217–1272":"1217–1272","1198–Female":"1198–Décédée","1217":"1217","1198":"1198","1230":"1230","1272":"1272","1184":"1184","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Karmine Manneville est née en 1198, à Hertfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Henry de Glanville."},"de":{"1198–":"1198–Verstorben","1184–1230":"1184–1230","1217–1272":"1217–1272","1198–Female":"1198–Verstorben","1217":"1217","1198"